<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="25" type="chorology">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Chorology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korge" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus peripherus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peripherus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Stenus peripherus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus melanarius" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanarius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Stenus melanarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Turkey (
<bibRefCitation author="Korge, H" journalOrPublisher="Annotationes Zoologicae et Botanicae" pageId="19" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 68" refId="B33" refString="Korge, H, 1971. Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Koleopterenfauna Kleinasiens. Annotationes Zoologicae et Botanicae 67: 1 - 68" title="Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Koleopterenfauna Kleinasiens." volume="67" year="1971">Korge 1971</bibRefCitation>
: 24), but only recently raised to species rank by 
<bibRefCitation author="Puthz, V" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitraege" pageId="19" pageNumber="36" pagination="137 - 230" refId="B60" refString="Puthz, V, 2008. Stenus Latreille und die segenreiche Himmelstochter (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Linzer biologische Beitraege 40 (1): 137 - 230" title="Stenus Latreille und die segenreiche Himmelstochter (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae)." volume="40" year="2008">Puthz (2008</bibRefCitation>
: 149). The species is distributed in eastern Turkey, Armenia, and Iran, where it reaches its southernmost known limit of distribution in the southern Talish at 
<geoCoordinate degrees="36" direction="north" minutes="54" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="36.9">36°54'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="49" direction="east" minutes="59" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="49.983334">49°59'E</geoCoordinate>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–18" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 13 - 18. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 13. Stenus guttula species group: ○ Stenus erythrocnemus, ● Stenus maculiger; 14. Stenus hopffgarteni species group: ○ Stenus fuscicornis; 15. Stenus humilis species group: ○ Stenus callidus; 16. Stenus impressus and Stenus incanus species groups: ○ Stenus heinzianus, △ Stenus taurus; 17. Stenus latifrons and Stenus melanarius species groups: ▲ Stenus latifrons, ○ Stenus incrassatus, □ Stenus morio, ● Stenus peripherus; 18. Stenus melanopus species group: ○ Stenus atratulus, ● Stenus piscator." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures13-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74430" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="25" type="biogeographical characterization">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Biogeographical characterization.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="25">
The few localities hitherto known suggest an expanded Caspian distribution for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korge" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus peripherus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peripherus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Stenus peripherus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
